    "Body": " Purpose Leads and oversees Traded and Non-Traded Market Risk for The Bank of Nova Scotia\u2019s Asia Pacific operations ensuring business strategies, plans and initiatives are executed / delivered in compliance with governing regulations, internal policies and procedures. Accountabilities? Leads and drives a customer focused culture throughout their team to deepen client relationships and leverage broader Bank relationships, systems and knowledge. Understand how the Bank\u2019s risk appetite and risk culture should be considered in day-to-day activities and decisions. Creates an environment in which his/her team pursues effective and efficient operations of his/her respective areas in accordance with Scotiabank\u2019s Values, its Code of Conduct and the Global Sales Principles, while ensuring the adequacy, adherence to and effectiveness of day-to-day business controls to meet obligations with respect to operational, compliance, AML/ATF/sanctions and conduct risk. Builds a high performance environment and implements a people strategy that attracts, retains, develops and motivates their team by fostering an inclusive work environment and using a coaching mindset and behaviours; communicating vison/values/business strategy; and, managing succession and development planning for the team. Communicates the Bank\u2019s risk appetite; regional risk exposures, strategies, policy and framework to key stakeholders including employees, the Board of Directors, regulators and external auditors. Communicates the Scotiabank risk culture within the Bank. Operate within a dynamic framework \u2013 which identifies, measures, monitors, opines on, independently values, and mitigates the Bank\u2019s material risks and guides decision making across the Bank. Provide ?market and counterparty risk oversight for all trading and non-trading ?operations:? Identification and assessment of risks, including monitoring for consistency with approved trading strategy. Development and implementation of risk measures and reporting. Development and evaluation of limit structures. Approval of limits and/or transactions within delegated authority. Ensuring portfolios are valued in line with Bank standards, including development, and documentation of independent price verification and valuation reserves. Ongoing analysis of risks, cash flow projections, and profit and loss. Review and approval of new products/services and making recommendations to the New Products Committee as required. Identification, escalation and resolution of risk issues arising from the activities noted above. Partner with the Business Lines in pursuit of their revenue-generating strategies and in line with the Bank\u2019s risk tolerances including: Provide market risk support for new business initiatives / expansion. Participate in committees / working groups relating to development and implementation of systems infrastructure. Ensure appropriate approvals, methodologies, controls and reporting in place for new products / business initiatives. Maintain open and regular communication with Business lines. Serves as a voting member of relevant risk management committees across Asia Pacific. Assesses financial and risk related management information requirements in the Bank and makes recommendations as required on business cases for enhanced/new technology infrastructure to support risk related management reporting and related internal controls. Designs and executes stress testing programs that support the risk appetite in the Bank, including challenge of the inputs and outputs and management action plans, and reports stress test results to Senior Management. In conjunction with Finance, develops and maintains the risk related information required as input for market risk capital allocation model for the Bank. In addition to supporting direct reports, the Head of Market Risk is required to provide necessary support and oversight to the in-country CROs on all market and liquidity risk matters. Regular communication is expected. Education / Experience / Other Information Requires at least a bachelor's degree in a related discipline. Master's degree, recognized Professional designation in a specialized area of finance or business or equivalent, is an asset. To be qualified to work as Head of Market Risk Asia requires over 10 years of progressively higher levels of responsibility and must possess expert: - Understanding of regulatory issues across Asia Pacific; - Leadership skills as demonstrated by the management of a team of risk management professionals ? In addition, the incumbent is required to keep abreast of political, economic, regulatory, tax, and legal developments, as well as funding issues. ", 
